values: I havent posted anything in a while. Still at Deleware elementry. Stared school. Busy LONG days.

I hate working in AMES Iowa. The job we are doing up there is FINALLY getting finished, so i'm going to be working at Delaware Elementary School in the Norwoodville area now. I'm getting interested in yoga.

June 5th, 2006. It's offical. $4 raise. 4 years of determination, learning, and hard work. Today I was sworn in as an offical Local 45 Sheet metal apprentice. Today is a big milestone in my life. Wish me luck.
It's friday. Awesome. I sign my papers of the apprenticeship on Monday. PAY INCREASE!!!
Well, I just got back from the bank. I took out a loan, and i'm buying this truck tomorow.

I just got back from Chicago with stephen. It was a wild and crazy adventure. We got to our hotel and found out they wouldnt let us stay because neither of us were 21. So I had my money refunded and stephen and I drove around Chicago for about 4 hours looking for the Crowne Plaza. After we found it, stephen and I were bent over by crowne plaza and raped severly moniteraly. It was all worth it. I am speechless as to the awesomeness of the show. I enjoyed Dragonforce 10,000 times more than I enjoyed Green day. I would have to say it was one of the best days of my life, thus far.

So, my work week is over. I'm done with my 4 ten hour days for the week. Tonight i'm gonna chill w/ tronic and colin @ colin's pad. Tomorow i'm going to sleep in and sit on my ass all day long. Awesome weekend, HERE I COME!!!
so I worked a 14 hour day today, and i'm in the apprenticeship... Daniel Murphy... pro badass...
Interviews tomorow... My future is held in the hands of 4 men...
it's official. I'm back home. I do not, repeat,do not live in my appartment in altoona any longer. My number is still the same though. New car, here I come...

"Bombs to set the people free, blood to feed the dollar tree, Flags for coffins on the screen, oil for the machine. Army of liberation, gunpoint indoctrination, The fires of sedation, Fulfill the prophecy."

so I had my test for my apprenticeship yesterday. I missed 4 out of 60. Which is awesome. Things are Looking Very promising for this whole thing. Danmikk will be mr. money mikk in about 4-5 years. RAP3!

Hopefully I get into this sheet metal apprentice ship. I think i've had a change of heart since my depression days, when I was missing alot of work and sleeping in and whatnot, but i've really turned things around, since I moved out to get a taste of what the real world is like. It's hard work. Keeping track of everything that you owe people, maintainence on your car and fridge, cleanliness, groceries, and many other things. I think that when Sarah's lease is up, I MIGHT move back home and finance a car, live @ home till I get a nice chunk of cash saved, pay off the loan on that car, and by then, stephen should deffinatley be back whereupon we make our living arrangements. I still don't know yet though. Everything is still up in the air. Once I find out if I'm getting in or not, plans will start to formulate. I hope everyone's year is going good.                               

                                                                   -Daniel
Ok, so it's really nice out today. That puts me in a very good mood. It's friday, which puts me in an EXTRA good mood. ROCK ON! DANMIKK, FTW!

financially, things seem like they are getting harder. IDK. I really could use a raise... but idk. My whole missing work situation seems like a thing of the past, which is good. I just wish that I would get notice by my own co-workers like the other trades notice my hard work on my job site.
uhhh, so, my car hasent been working for the past 3 months or so... IT'S GETTING FIXED!!!! YES, no more bumming rides anymore! FOR THE WIN!!!

I went to work this morning. It sucked ass. I woke up way to early. I was violently awakened from my slumber by my damned alarm. I wanted to throw it into muck. But, i didnt. I meandered to the living room, where i put on pants. The thought of me sleeping happily in a forest with chipmunks and bunny rabbits ran through my head like a motion picture. Then came the shirt. Socks shortly there after, followed up by boots. A string of cuss-words about being so damn tired, and out the door i went. 

Down the stairs, and to the sidewalk. Pull out the keys. Slip them into the lock. Turn, click, open. ****...i left my helmet in my apartment. Back up the stairs. Click, thug, click, thud...open. There is my helmet. A somber reminder of my hapless existence. Back down the stairs i drag myself. 

Driving. I hate driving to work. The street lights. I count them. 476 till i get to work. It doesnt have the same effect on the way home. 

I hate my boss

      Everyone should go out and download the song "piece of shit car" by Adam Sandler. That's how I feel about my piece of shit.

called in today. Brian is such an asshole. He never gives me any credit. OH well, I've only called in like 2 times this month. If he wants caulking done so bad, he can do it himself. Anyways, it's almost christmas, which is cool. Hope I get what I want. Hope everyone has a good holiday!

I wish I could have somthing really profound to say, but I don't. I live a very bland life. It seems like I try to hard to find myself. I think way toooo much. I place random thoughts where I will. I've found myself lately wanting to have a significant other. I miss spending my time w/ a/that special someone. Making memories. Thanking god i'm alive. Perhaps It's not the best thing for me right now... who knows. SHould I stop being dormant? Is taking action what I should be doing right now? The world is harsh my friends... cast all your cares upon me
The heart is deciteful above all things.

well, it turns out I don't hate my car. We just had a small 3 week fight. We made up today, she pur's like a kitten again. I LOVE YOU CAR! oh yeah, stephen and I made the most bad ass dinner tonight. FTW!
If I had the strength to lift my car up, I would swing it against a tree as hard as I could. I hate my car.
Hung out w/ BT, Valerie Strait, Janice, and stephen tonight. It was fun fun fun! yay
I put my tongue barbell back in.... wow.

Work=Suck. Today so far=Suck. I want the weekend to come. It seems like that's what I wait my entire work week for is the weekend, and it's gone so fast. I hate working. I just want to sit on my ass and get paid alot of money, but so does everyone. "and you shall toil the ground by the sweat of your brow"
Painful Memories have now Resurfaced. I hope it's not true...

What made my day.

Driving home from work, I see gorgeous looking girl in opposing lane w/ her hand cutting through the air. Arm resting on the door. I, like the sly humorous devil that I am, Reach my hand as far out as I can and try to give her a high Five, as she drives past. I didnt get it, but it's the principal that counts. I grabed her attention. She waved, as I look in my rear view mirror. Day=made.
I caught a pick from jimmy eat world, and almost got up on stage to play the bass. It was awesome. I love live music. w007.
